    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Elevated stands enclosed by a guardrail and a platform on which to rest a book, intended for clergy to preach to the congregation; usually situated within a church and may be fixed or movable (movable pulpit). It often has a staircase, a backboard, and a sounding-board.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
